[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating class proxies and inline testing**\n\nI'm facing a challenge with an active class needing an inline setup, but it seems the preflight checks are pointing to issues with the proxy mock maker. If the resource set is a proxy, the active class isn't being reached. I wonder if I should create a dedicated test for configuring inline or if it's better to focus on using the public API. But, it looks like there may be limitations with Native Image contracts for instrumentation. The task is asking for improvements, but if it's impossible, perhaps I need to reassess our approach.\n\n**Considering Mockito with Native Image**\n\nI'm wondering if ByteBuddyAgent.install might fail in a native context. It seems the constructor could catch errors and invoke ToolProvider reflectively, leading to issues. While the public API allows using Mockito.mock(Class) with the inline maker, it wouldn't work in native. I could create a dedicated JUnit test for the class, but there's a challenge with the resource forcing inline for that test. It might be useful to inspect plugins to see if there's a way around this.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_04090fb7cff6e1e7016a3a85e0fd0081959b4d935fd73a393f\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqOoXy6pxiLo2JNdqNUZ2XPUMqJCfJms2V5jR3W0iMj2RDlDR__cQUEZPdgE6AB3uQcAbofDXcgiTkJ5y1Lx3uecgk5UbQ0iXmYdOzjeX1MtuxjsXn_bctu-UOoHn4XGsUFA0jOHO7kxFf0WaOYlEBTQE8PdMHxdhgmK2Uwxk9MGThfqz71v6-Ju4ICXoo_SQXnjVDiYscu78w2EW4NG_8ieGd3Qh8V7vTgOmHm9OQSM4Tq5HGQww1RIfkS7BV_evjm978ucJC9foX1zbGJs6Ox_j0bLq_XD3mPhGi11F3-5K2vpJ3a5k2mPcwr3xQw5yyx5KrRt4IMtIhotWSkTzqLO22cb35mViLLzCrhes5xn5N0Qyjjv7LjHmr8eB5VNrNtiRTgfVKFOigYZYu6wzDD5bf5Oy-ax5kBIb2PAYjwHFIf_kEkzpsH-ggCXDdcczkjmf8y_61gbpj2g4J_uWjf1oi7Q4MVW936TctKF1tKBnP1TGm1LLLlHjqbJ9oZWjz7xTRPR1NSNd63LIfWd7gcBWQjwDCbwodXQpsjOzA63iUgBq_7RV72sGAQhO1HneHrU_vZYzOBr245d23B_YGyLaEKfznyFlH2ytEfulVAz