[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring class loading strategies**\n\nI'm thinking about extending the URLClassLoader. One idea is to use the parent ClassLoader to access the JDK through ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader(). This could be useful for certain tasks. I also wonder about loading classes child-first for specific libraries like org.mockito and net.bytebuddy. It's interesting to consider what happens if ByteBuddyAgent comes from the parent. There’s definitely some potential here with different loading strategies.\n\n**Considering build.gradle modifications**\n\nI think I need to add native runtime arguments for `java.class.path` in the `build.gradle` file to make child loading work in my native attempt. This support file is needed inside the target, particularly for new tests. However, I wonder if it's really necessary. I know that the child loader in the JVM uses the system classpath, so if I set it for native, it will include the jar paths.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_04090fb7cff6e1e7016a3a8941b7d4819597d748c068cba5d9\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqOomup2kQLZ-uPkv7Tqo4ry9Y0qQdCHS6_xPDsYo7Us1Rhxxi1gV7kDr5_g-r5VlLC46JEOHNomk_rf61hqxP5ea18B-zsgZOFCHycm-MiQawhVfIIcgPs_H_06I2Um_Vjwleaaxnq7hUXv_LphZ1unCOwAVHO2NukgJtNhWchc_IUB2qq--6Feqs3rWuFAqWqQZqHki38vJvG8RE8-ceZ0TH5KLhIG88HY19iXqm9-SlpA-AgX8E1QEps8FsKGTtPfQo-43EVVTZgaASJ6gJzaQ1QkBNfc0FkH7Tk-SkrLSnZjeFxoLta6yQoYzRbyxuYYvLco74Ew6Lj_uA5QsHTL7CigfuW5G9h9QuIY2ZZeC0JOzNrACRVBXUaoCdGG2pxPWnT-ZeBpcGqT1tzpiad3z_NkASWvNZ-R9CA4k3pwOqPu66QioiEK6lEFhC1ZXNIDLDR8WjreaXm31uMoL2KQUEZ9WaVRIMfKO4rlIGFtVFAoRBdQj62mlCtx6-0tVx3OTkYkiomXJUxEbM1LQGpTOmNvC_jRd-PurEeUJZ4DBviy6yC7wl5hgwq7i4tgvtHmFj8i4LKgL97HzgB6T_ea7ReNhuNM234E_6mujwQ1dL7sadszhOwoJQgDXrlPJAk202k4YhTQ8IcI3ymeKAogratEl9yHUXAwop85rgYThsZdslVQixUT7bJLxz8V6j9JChkdXcoCrTcY87kWmgVeKXDdYkZSJzyLZ3sX7TVJdvPkzSkWkeVbhWZi09lCHa9iO-ycVGd64e9PPrF1lq5Pe9NF