o4qFslTBISzunybB3mhqdnP6ksypLRgiQBe_1LNZq7D_fFuMpeeq_QSYsPZdiKbJd5X2kMJOSnv1S6obQo-nAQryJoXEOxLcKOpffk-P95wwF2OcbNbT7134FfZW4ZXHIPoc6_nwaAsn0aCtyFz0iDz6_soBVe9NsuDF5qt21m8qraIwRFmzAdapsqUdU4kCQPAItOh5MYs8V9Z9CFALy4GlKqZ4zurmzLIWZDD8f3bj4zTwcJH2LGP6h_hr1LhLIkVElia_W88J4Rx8lpcvmtDZe4gTbLJZN5hFtnm_ZvkrkFmUh6fElQeScAcQx9p8TnDBKneHWBvoePGGjQQv7Jb0rWqpUFqGVGm4ijXTzHJ0H0GuGqyOE_rlzw2ywVRv1gEfFZ_6aASS56s4J9QL0IYcMD2TZN5d3gD1GayEZRJuD-jS8jvzMrvbVOORnbyGpoc3XX3P_mhgMIE_V3RUk=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class loading strategies**\\n\\nI'm thinking about extending the URLClassLoader. One idea is to use the parent ClassLoader to access the JDK through ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader(). This could be useful for certain tasks. I also wonder about loading classes child-first for specific libraries like org.mockito and net.bytebuddy. It's interesting to consider what happens if ByteBuddyAgent comes from the parent. There’s definitely some potential here with different loading strategies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering build.gradle modifications**\\n\\nI think I need to add native runtime arguments for `java.class.path` in the `build.gradle` file to make child loading work in my native attempt. This support file is needed inside the target, particularly for new tests. However, I wonder if it's really necessary. I know that the child loader in the JVM uses the system classpath, so if I set it for native, it will include the jar paths.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2DVbAjnMlB5pnsdQjWOFEH7V|fc_04090fb7cff6e1e7016a3a89ae64b08195ab29f0fcb5b24d5d", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "            buildArgs.add('-Dnet.bytebuddy.experimental=true')\n            runtimeArgs('-Dnet.bytebuddy.experimental=true')", "newText": "            buildArgs.add('-Dnet.bytebuddy.experimental=true')\n            runtimeArgs('-Dnet.bytebuddy.experimental=true')\n            runtimeArgs(\"-Djava.class.path=${sourceSets.test.runtimeClasspath.asPath}\")"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1234, "output": 2306, "cacheRead": 65024, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 68564, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782221089900, "responseId": "resp_04090fb7cff6e1e7016a3a89232ac08195ba7a7077820de5b3"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_2DVbAjnMlB5pnsdQjWOFEH7V|fc_04090fb7cff6e1e7016a3a89ae64b08195ab29f0fcb5b24d5d", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/build.gradle."}], "details": {"diff": "    ...\n 30     binaries {\n 31         test {\n 32             buildArgs.add('-Dnet.bytebuddy.experimental=true')\n 33             runtimeArgs('-Dnet.bytebuddy.experimental=true')\n+34             runtimeArgs(\"-Djava.class.path=${sourceSets.test.runtimeClasspath.asPath}\")\n 34         }\n 35     }\n 36 \n 37     agent {\n    ...", "firstChangedLine": 34}, "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782221232846}]}
