[assistant] Fixed the `ClassCastException` failure.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - `MockUtil.getMockMaker()` loads explicit mock makers via `Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader()`.
[assistant] - The test loaded Mockito classes in a child-first classloader, but did not set that loader as the thread context classloader.
[assistant] - As a result, Mockito’s child-loaded `MockMaker` interface was compared against an `InlineByteBuddyMockMaker` loaded from the parent/system loader, causing:
[assistant]   - `ClassCastException`
[assistant]   - `Failed to load MockMaker: mock-maker-inline`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changes made in `tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMakerTest.java`:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Set the thread context classloader to the child-first Mockito classloader for both inline mock maker tests.
[assistant] - Restore the previous context classloader in `finally`.
[assistant] - Invoke `MockingDetails` and `MockitoFramework` methods through their public interfaces from the same child classloader.
[assistant] - Relaxed the initialization failure assertion to check the full stack trace for `Could not initialize inline Byte Buddy mock maker`, because Mockito may wrap that initialization error in a higher-level `Failed to construct MockMaker` exception.
[assistant] 
[assistant] No metadata files were edited. Tests were not run.
